    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-26T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="196"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119 P 43/924: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-26T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 26, 1918—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>71. Your 123 November 19, 7 p.m. Suggestion that <persName corresp="#p_GHS1"
                        >Gibson</persName> remain in Austria with headquarters in Vienna approved.
                    Not thought advisable to open Embassy Chancery. It is presumed <persName
                        corresp="#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName> will open headquarters’ office in Vienna
                    and <persName corresp="#p_GHS1">Gibson</persName> should be able to use that
                    office in the capacity of assistant to <persName corresp="#p_HHC1"
                        >Hoover</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
